    <div align='center'>
        <font size='4'><b>ADVENTURES CLOSE TO HOME</b></font><br>
                                <img src='http://graphics.millsberry.com/site_gfx/interiors/gazette/gazette_20080828.jpg' border='1' width='280' height='200'>
                        </div>
        <div id='gazette_byline'><em>By Audrey Smythe-Wei<br>Staff Writer</em></div>
        <b>Thursday, August 28, 2008</b> &mdash;
    Sometimes you don&#039;t have to go very far to find adventure.<br><br>In past articles, we&#039;ve talked about different adventures you can take outside of Millsberry, but there&#039;s one that&#039;s a bit closer to home.<br><br>In fact, you&#039;re already on it right now.<br><br>If you haven&#039;t guessed it yet, reading is one of the easiest ways to go on a great adventure. The adventure is in your mind. <br><br>Carla Robbins, the owner of Book Ends is, what some would call, heavily invested reading. <br><br>When asked why reading is so special to her, she replied, &quot;The greatest thing about reading is the freedom you have to imagine the story any way you want.&quot;<br><br>&quot;The author writes the story and provides the description, but it&#039;s you who pictures it in your mind. You get to visualize all of the details and the action.&quot; <br><br>&quot;There&#039;s actually a great new book we just got in. It&#039;s a really good example of using your imagination for fun and personal entertainment.&quot;<br><br>
<br>
&quot;The way you imagine the story will be completely different from the way anyone else does, so it becomes your story. It&#039;s personal to you.&quot;<br><br>&quot;In that way, you become part of the story, too.&quot;<br><br>This is the main reason some people prefer reading to watching TV or movies, or playing video games. <br><br>It&#039;s amazing to discover the fun and adventures you can have in your mind, all you need is a book. Some people can spend an entire day curled up in a chair with a good book. <br><br>&quot;I can usually just read for hours on end.&quot; said Mrs. Fiddle, the head Librarian at the Millsberry Academy Library. <br><br>&quot;I always find it astonishing how words on a page can turn into the most amazing story that is just as real as any movie or TV show.&quot;<br><br>Another great thing about reading is that, unlike watching TV, you can do it anywhere. Half of the fun is picking a great place to read. <br><br>&quot;When the weather&#039;s nice, I really love to read under a Tree. During the winter, reading next to the fireplace is also a treat&quot;, added Carla.<br><br>So if you want to journey across the world and meet amazing people, you don&#039;t need a plane ticket - just a library card. <br><br>
